I received your sample box and I'm blown away by the products. They are incredible! The quality seems very high, the possibilities for customization and branding....mind-blowing. I am beyond impressed. Add in the fact that it's all compostable/recyclable/recycled/sustainable/eco-friendly - too amazing. The only thing I had an issue with (and it might be my browser??) was the custom design sample portion of the site. It would not work for me. It kept freezing or adjustments wouldn't show up. I was just playing, so it wasn't a big deal, but when I get my designs finalized I hope it's a little easier to work with. Thank you so much - super super impressed and excited to find you!

Maybe it can be good to rethink about the closure of the ink pad, or simply had a piece of tape so it won't open and bleed.. funny for a brand named NoIssue that customers are facing some issues ;)
But don't worry, it won't stop me to buy again from NoIssue !

Not send them from China? China is not a country that I associate with sustainability and I was quite surprised when my delivery was sent from there. I thought they were coming from NZ, actually. Unless you're visiting Chinese factories regularly you can't be sure you're getting what you think you are or that people are being treated correctly. Sustainability is not just about the materials used - it's a lot to do with people as well. Still rating you a 10 since I should have asked and the price is still equivalent to what I can source myself from China if I were so inclined. My 10 is directly related to price but I have 500 sheets to think about whether I'll use an Australian manufacturer next time instead. :)

This is not a big deal as the actual stamp still comes out the same :) 

Another thing, I wish the website was more clear on the file submission and would recommend that users submit a vector.  I was previously unfamiliar with making vector files so I was excited to see that they were not a requirement on noissue, however, the stamp designs that were created from the images I sent were really rough due to the automatic vectoring process and in the end, I was asked to submit my own vector.  If I had known ahead of time, it would have been much easier.

Overall though, I love the products and will definitely order again now that I am familiar with the process!
